title: The quadratic equation $$h=16t^2+vt+h_0$$ models the height of a volleyball hit straight upwards with initial velocity $$176$$ feet per second from a height of $$4$$ feet. $$h$$ is the height of the volleyball, $$t$$ is the time, v is the initial velocity, and $$h_0$$ is the initial height.
lesson: 10.5 Graphing Quadratic Equations in Two Variables
